comments: Sometimes it was ambiguous whether two people who liked to do something "after work" shared a workplace, or if two people who lived "on the same floor/building" were roommates. This might have been intentional for the purpose of the study, but I thought it was worth noting since sometimes it was more clear (ie. referring to "[both of] their work/office")
Thank you for the opportunity to participate!
